20/11/2005
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- The UN's special envoy for Kosovo status talks, former Finnish president Martti Ahtisaari, is expected to arrive Monday (21 November) on a two-day visit in Kosovo.
It will mark the start of a regional trip that also includes stops in Belgrade, Podgorica, Skopje and Tirana.
According to the envoy, his goal during the tour is to hear the positions of all sides involved in the Kosovo issue.
(Beta, RTS - 20/11/05)
